Intelligent Home Skill offers the most comprehensive voice controlled smart home experience with Alexa. Control your home lighting hands free. Just say it, Intelligent Home will obey. 

Here’s a step by step guide:
(1). Download our "Intelligent Home" app in Google Play or iOS App Store:
iOS App Store: https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/id1221180183
Google Play: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.intelligent.home
(2). Launch the app and register a new account (or login if you’re already registered);
(3). Turn on Intelligent Home devices and connect them with “Intelligent Home” app;
(4). IMPORTANT: You can rename the devices with Intelligent Home App. So if you rename a smart bulb “smart socket”, then Echo will get that same name after discovered the devices in Step 8;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from Amazon Market, Google Play or iOS App Store, and connect Echo with "Alexa" app;
(6). Search the Alexa Skills directory for "Intelligent Home";
(7). Click Enable skill of "Intelligent Home", then input your account username, password and region on the linking page;
(8). Talk to Echo "“Alexa,discover devices.”. Wait till Echo says "Discover is completed";
(9). Now all setup is done. Try talk to Echo to control your devices.

You can control your device like this:
Alexa, descover devices;
Alexa, turn on smart socket;
Alexa, turn off smart socket;
